						<summary>

						<p>Slab set up in front of the Nāgēśvarasvāmi temple.</p>						

						<p>PRATĀPARUDRADĒVA.</p>						

						<p>1308 A.D.</p>						

						<p>This inscription is dated Śaka [12]30, Kārttīka, śu. 12, corresponding to October 27, Sunday 1308 A.D.</p>						

						<p>Damaged. Registers the gift of wet land to the temple of Mūlasthāna Nāganāṁthadēva at Krānāla by <hi rend="italic">sakala sēnādhipati Rāyapaṭṭasāhiṇi</hi> (Juṭṭaya) leṁka, who was ruling Mulkināṁḍi, Penāpāḍi, Pottapināḍu, Peḍakallu and Nāṁttavāḍi (from) Ghaṇḍikoṭa, for maintaining the (worship) of the god and for the salaries <hi rend="italic">(jītamu)</hi> of some persons probably temple servants (namess not mentioned). The <hi rend="italic">prabhus</hi> of Sirivrōḍla sthala and <hi rend="italic">samasta prajas</hi> have also remitted the tax of one Kunṭa probably to the temple.</p>						

						</summary>
